    <h1>All-in-one Digital Growth Portal</h1>

    <p>Your dashboard is the central place to manage your Wikimint account and keep track of everything that supports your online business growth. Whether you're a new member or an experienced marketer, you'll find the most important information and tools in one convenient location.</p>

    <img  loading="lazy" src="/assets/images/others/wikimint-all-in-one-marketing-platform.webp" alt="All-in-one digital marketing platform for creating funnels, promoting websites, collecting leads, tracking analytics, earning credits, and growing an online business." title="All-in-One Marketing Platform for Online Business Growth" class="w-full" />


<p>At the top of the page, you can quickly review your available credits, Growth Units, earnings, referrals, and membership status. These summary cards give you an instant overview of your account so you always know where you stand.</p>

<p>Use the Workspace section to access the features you use most often. You can create new promotions, manage your wallet, buy or sell Growth Units, generate short links, invite referrals, request withdrawals, and access helpful resources without searching through menus.</p>

<p>The activity area keeps you informed about your recent account actions, including earnings, promotions, transactions, and important updates. Your profile section highlights your completion progress, making it easy to identify information that can strengthen your account and improve your visibility within the community.</p>

<p>Don't forget to share your personal referral link to introduce others to Wikimint. Every successful referral helps expand your network while creating additional earning opportunities.</p>

<p>As new features become available, you'll also find announcements, business resources, tutorials, and practical guides designed to help you make the most of the platform. Checking your dashboard regularly helps you stay informed, monitor your progress, and take advantage of new opportunities as they are introduced.</p>

<p>Whether your goal is generating more traffic, promoting your business, building passive income, or expanding your online presence, your Wikimint dashboard provides the tools and insights needed to move forward with confidence. Make it your starting point each time you sign in and continue building your business one step at a time.</p>

    <section id="faq" class="hr bg-white">

        <h2>
          Frequently Asked Questions
        </h2>
    
     
    
    
    
              
              <div class="acc space-y-4">
    
                <div class="space-y-4" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage">
                <div class="acc-item">
                  <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q1" checked>
                  <div itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                    <label for="q1" class="acc-title">
                      <h3 itemprop="name" class="text-lg">What is the Wikimint Marketing Platform?</h3>
                    </label>
                      <div itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="acc-content">
                        <p  itemprop="text">
                            The Wikimint Marketing Platform helps members promote their business, products, services, websites, and affiliate offers from one place. Every account includes tools that support online promotion, personal branding, lead generation, and campaign management. Members can build multiple funnels, monitor performance, earn credits through platform activities, and take part in community-based earning opportunities while growing their online presence.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              
                <div class="acc-item">
                  <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q2">
                  <div itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                    <label for="q2" class="acc-title">
                      <h3 itemprop="name" class="text-lg">Why should I complete my public profile?</h3>
                    </label>
                      <div itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="acc-content">
                        <p itemprop="text">
                            Your public profile is much more than a personal introduction. It acts as a promotional page that you can share on social media, business cards, messaging apps, email signatures, or anywhere online. Visitors can learn about your business, view your recommended links, follow your social profiles, and join your email list through the integrated opt-in form. Every member receives the same public profile opportunity regardless of membership level.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="acc-item">
                  <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q3">
                  <div itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                    <label for="q3" class="acc-title">
                      <h3 itemprop="name" class="text-lg">What are credits and why are they important?</h3>
                    </label>
                      <div itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="acc-content">
                        <p itemprop="text">
                            Credits are one of the key parts of the Wikimint Marketing Platform. They measure your participation and can influence several platform benefits. Credits are used when calculating member rewards, promotional opportunities, referral placement, and other activities that depend on account participation. Staying active and building your credit balance helps your account receive greater exposure across the platform.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="acc-item">
                  <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q4">
                  <div itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                    <label for="q4" class="acc-title">
                      <h3 itemprop="name" class="text-lg">How can I earn credits?</h3>
                    </label>
                      <div itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="acc-content">
                        <p itemprop="text">
                            Members earn credits by taking part in approved platform activities and participating in the advertising section. Credits may also increase through pooled earnings that are distributed according to the quality of Wikimint article revenue and each member's credit balance. Regular participation helps build your account over time and increases your eligibility for several platform features and promotional opportunities.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="acc-item">
                  <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q5">
                  <div itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                    <label for="q5" class="acc-title">
                      <h3 itemprop="name" class="text-lg">What benefits do Pro members receive?</h3>
                    </label>
                      <div itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="acc-content">
                        <p itemprop="text">
                            Pro members receive additional promotional advantages that help their campaigns reach a larger audience. Their links may appear more frequently within supported rotation areas, giving greater visibility compared to free accounts. Pro membership is intended for members who actively promote products, services, affiliate offers, or business websites and would like additional promotional opportunities while continuing to earn credits.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="acc-item">
                  <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q6">
                  <div itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
                    <label for="q6" class="acc-title">
                      <h3 itemprop="name" class="text-lg">What can Free members do on the platform?</h3>
                    </label>
                      <div itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="acc-content">
                        <p itemprop="text">
                            Free members have access to many valuable features. They receive a public profile page, can build their personal brand, promote one primary website, add multiple recommended links, display a LeadsLeap email opt-in form, publish website and product reviews with their own affiliate links, earn credits through participation, and qualify for pooled earnings based on their credit balance. Free members may also receive spillover referrals.
                        </p>
                      </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
    
              <div class="acc-item">
                <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q7">
                <label for="q7" class="acc-title">
                  <h3 class="text-lg">How does the affiliate program and spillover referral system work?</h3>
                </label>
                  <div class="acc-content">
                    <p>
                        Every registered member can recommend the Wikimint Marketing Platform and earn referral commissions when eligible. Members who join without a referrer may be assigned as spillover referrals according to platform rules that consider account participation and credit balance. This approach rewards active members while giving both Free and Pro accounts an opportunity to receive additional referrals over time.
                    </p>
                  </div>
              </div>
    
              <div class="acc-item">
                <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q8">
                <label for="q8" class="acc-title">
                  <h3 class="text-lg">What types of funnels can I create?</h3>
                </label>
                  <div class="acc-content">
                    <p>
                        Members can build multiple funnels for different marketing goals. A funnel may promote a landing page, sales page, opt-in page, affiliate offer, personal website, business website, product, service, or another approved destination. Creating separate funnels allows members to organize campaigns for different audiences and measure results more effectively from the dashboard.
                    </p>
                  </div>
              </div>

              <div class="acc-item">
                <input type="radio" name="acc" id="q9">
                <label for="q9" class="acc-title">
                  <h3 class="text-lg">Can I promote my own websites and affiliate links?</h3>
                </label>
                  <div class="acc-content">
                    <p>
                        Yes. Members may add one primary website along with multiple recommended links that point to approved websites, products, or affiliate offers. Important social profiles such as Facebook, X, and LinkedIn can also be included on the public profile page. Built-in analytics help members monitor page activity and understand how visitors interact with their profile and promotional links.
                    </p>
                  </div>
              </div>

